{"body_text": "Depends on PR #1121\n\n\nConverts the [Create|Edit|Clone][Recipe|Extension]Page components over to the template method pattern\n\nAll pages with forms inherit from AbstractFormPage, which handles common validation functionality which was otherwise duplicated across each component\nPages define a handful of 'abstract' functions (getTitle, getFormComponent, etc), which are called in AbstractFormPage.render\n\n\n\nThis cuts down on a lot of copy-pasted code across each page, however I wonder if the abstraction adds an unnecessary layer of complexity.", "labels": [], "number": 1127, "assignee": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/andymikulski", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/2767162?v=4", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "andymikulski", "type": "User", "id": 2767162, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andymikulski/followers"}, "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy", "closed_at": "2017-12-07T21:25:09Z", "body_html": "<ul>\n<li>\n<p><del>Depends on PR <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"270020679\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/issues/1121\" href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1121\">#1121</a></del></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Converts the <code>[Create|Edit|Clone][Recipe|Extension]Page</code> components over to the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template_method_pattern\" rel=\"nofollow\">template method pattern</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>All pages with forms inherit from <code>AbstractFormPage</code>, which handles common validation functionality which was otherwise duplicated across each component</li>\n<li>Pages define a handful of 'abstract' functions (<code>getTitle</code>, <code>getFormComponent</code>, etc), which are called in <code>AbstractFormPage.render</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This cuts down on a lot of copy-pasted code across each page, however I wonder if the abstraction adds an unnecessary layer of complexity.</p>", "id": 272006190, "title": "Generic form components", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/1127", "diff_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1127.diff", "html_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1127", "patch_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1127.patch"}, "comments": 10, "state": "closed", "body": "- ~Depends on PR #1121~\r\n\r\n- Converts the `[Create|Edit|Clone][Recipe|Extension]Page` components over to the [template method pattern](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template_method_pattern)\r\n  - All pages with forms inherit from `AbstractFormPage`, which handles common validation functionality which was otherwise duplicated across each component\r\n   - Pages define a handful of 'abstract' functions (`getTitle`, `getFormComponent`, etc), which are called in `AbstractFormPage.render`\r\n\r\nThis cuts down on a lot of copy-pasted code across each page, however I wonder if the abstraction adds an unnecessary layer of complexity. ", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/1127/events", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/1127/labels{/name}", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "comments_ur